rComments: Great class. The content is interesting and well presented, and the Prof is loveable. He really cares about his students and deserves more recognition. Tests usually consist of one or two questions, and the final is lengthy.

By far one of the nicest profs I've ever had. His passion in the subjects he teaches is very clear, he makes things easy to understand and a class like histoire du cinema fun and interesting. The FASTEST grader i have ever had, I think he graded my midterm in a weekend. Made the class extremely accessible throughout the semester, very flexible!

I enjoyed Professor Grandena's class quite a bit, even though it was a Monday morning 8:30! Although he was a little disorganized and we missed classes because of it, he is very knowledgeable, gives solid lectures and is a fair marker. Open book exams were easy enough if you came to class and took notes. Would recommend if interested in film!

He is simply great i took the cinema introduction class as an optionsp course and didnt miss one class! I was in biochemistry and allthough i'm a science nerd, i also happen to habe a hobby for cinematography. I even like this course more than my biochemistry cursus classes
Awesome professor, really nice and friendly!  would take his classes again anytime!
Great prof! Loved his lectures and class. Very clear and precise. One of my favourite profs!

My favourite prof at uOttawa by far. Amazing prof. He's very comical, sweet and always in a good mood, which always improves a class. He has highly engaging lectures that are never boring. You learn a lot about the history of cinema and watch some incredibly interesting and artistic films.
There is nothing from the textbook in the exams. His class is boring as sht. If you just take cinema class as a selective, I highly recommend Italian Cinema class rather than this one
really good.
Fantastic class. Prof is great and knowledgable, always available outside class. Highly recommended.

Very engaging lectures. Really enjoyed class. But professor was never available outside of class. After missing class due to a death in family, professor was not helpful. Did not deduct any marks - but did not help me catch up.

Very helpful teacher. His explanations are very clear and precise. Great sense of humour and is very understanding. I have a DEC in film studies and I can tell you, he knows what he's talking about. Loved it. Great experience! Take any class he teaches, you won't regret!

As one of his students this year, I learned a lot from him... He is an excellent teacher, explains everything very clearly and with great humor. He doesn't put his PWP online, but makes sure everyone got to write the entire thing down. Un Français vraiment pas trop chiant! :)
Prof. Grandena was an excellent teacher, very clear on rules and expectation. His class was really fun, but you still have to study hard.
He knows his stuff! Great prof, great guy!

One word: awesome. Je l'ai eu pour 4 cours et je prendrais son cours encore n'importe quand. Il est passioné par le cinéma et nous donne de bons exemples avec des explications claires. Ses examens peuvent être difficiles, mais il s'agit de comprendre la matiere et appliquer a un sujet.

C'est un professeur très relaxe en classe et très drôle. En cours de cinéma, il est très agréable et commente beaucoup. Beaucoup de lectures à faire, mais on peut facilement les survoler rapidement. Examens courts et faciles. Très bon prof!
I had him for New Media and Globalization. Some of the material was very similar! He is a good prof, keeps things funny and serious at the same time. Lots of opinions!
Really great teacher!! really funny too!!

Sooo easy! Wow, a few quizzes (instead of a midterm), and they r all opinionated, u can disagree w class content.He have me extra 10% on final grade cos i did a presentation. V. funny, and friendly. do NOT fake some1's name on attendance - FLIPS out and swears! V. scary!!!

Very interesting stuff covered in this class (New Media). Very good lectures and a good sense of direction, things connect well. Tests very reasonable and cover major themes rather than quotes on pages.
Amazing.
Great class. I liked the fact that he let us choose any movie we wanted to do our mid-term and final papers on.
